The paper proposes a method for simplifying the auto-regressive generation process using a confidence-based approximation. This method can be applied to various data domains, including sequences and images. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a predictor, which suggests the involvement of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the computational cost reduction, which could be related to cs.SD (Software Engineering).
